    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-05-16T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-05-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="371"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d371">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Lord Lyons</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Seward</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-05-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 16, 1864.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Sir</hi>: Another week has passed, and the British
                    subjects taken on board British vessels seized for breach of blockade are still
                    in prison. I must beg you to look back to my letter of the 9th, and I must
                    express a hope that you will at least enable me to inform her Majesty’s
                    government, by the mail of to-morrow, that the <hi rend="italic">five</hi> men
                    lately belonging to the Don, who have been so long confined in the Ludlow street
                    jail, have at last been set free.</p>
                <p>Believe me to be, my dear sir, your very faithful, humble servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>LYONS.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">William H. Seward</hi>, <hi rend="italic">&amp;c.,
                            &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
